reviews.review_text:
Bobby and Jerry at their Best I'm amazed this show hasn't received total acclaim. The second set showcases some of the Dead's tightest, most energized jams ever. Scarlet into Mountain is flawless. Estimated rocks with amazing conviction. The drums take it down to primal beats that had everyone howling with joy. Out of 20 years of shows this was the best for me. 

Thank you, thank you, thank you, for having it here!
Some of the best bottom end iv'e heard from this early of period. Dare I say that this taper upstaged the Oade brothers. The bottom end is solid and rumbles through my hardwood floor.
Lesh Zone of Bass Dug and Bolewski are right.  Listen up.

Woofer Workout Oh yea, you got 'dat right. The 100k and below be fine in heah. Nice heavy lower end recording. My hand made in Dusseldorf cabinets are getting a transfusion o' bass with this one. Somethig to bug the heavy metal neighbors with. Yea, Buddy.

Thanks taper! Fine job. Nice setlist (I'm a Walkin' The Dog fan) and The Boys were present for this show. I don't sling 5's around like candy.

-Pulver
